## Template Filtering

This project demonstrates template filtering. You can generate subsets of files using:

```bash
# Generate only core services
yagen -c config.yaml -d data.json --include "Core Infrastructure"

# Generate only API services
yagen -c config.yaml -d data.json --include "API Services"

# Exclude debug utilities
yagen -c config.yaml -d data.json --exclude "Debug*"

# Exclude all tests
yagen -c config.yaml -d data.json --exclude "*Test*"

# Generate only tests
yagen -c config.yaml -d data.json --include "*Test*"

# Use regex patterns
yagen -c config.yaml -d data.json --include "regex:^(Core|API).*"
```

## Generated Structure

When all templates are generated:

```
output/
├── core/           # Core infrastructure services
├── api/            # API services
├── debug/          # Debug utilities
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/       # Unit tests
│   └── integration/# Integration tests
└── docs/           # Documentation
```
